title: Troubled New Zealand wildlife park euthanizes two lions, fate of five more unclear
summary: Members of the public are urging for the protection of the last lions at a sanctuary facing potential euthanasia. Former staff are also advocating for a reconsideration of the decision to put the lions down. The situation has sparked widespread concern and calls for intervention.

title: US to cut airline traffic by 10% due to shutdown, Trump transport chief says
summary: Sean Duffy announced that cuts at 40 locations to alleviate stress on air traffic controllers will begin on Friday if no solution is reached. The measure aims to address ongoing issues within the air traffic control system. Duffy emphasized the urgency of finding a resolution to prevent these cuts.

title: Kentucky plane crash: death toll rises to 12 as officials investigate how engine detached
summary: NTSB agents have arrived in Louisville to investigate the incident involving a UPS cargo plane that experienced engine detachment and a fire on its left wing. The investigation aims to determine the cause of the malfunctions during flight. The safety of cargo operations and the handling of such emergencies will be assessed as part of the inquiry.

title: Trump goes on posting frenzy a day after Democrats win key elections
summary: President shares over 30 posts on Truth Social in just a few hours, featuring a mix of content. Among these are a series of strange AI-generated videos that garnered attention. The rapid posting raises questions about the nature and intent behind the shared content.
